Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 989 "The \NCase of Ayumi's Illustrated Diary"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.33,0:00:03.77,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,"Saturday, December 5th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:07.51,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Today Conan-kun caught a jewel thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.08,0:00:13.70,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked him how he did it, he said \Nit was thanks to my illustrated diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.14,0:00:16.69,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't remember figuring anything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.69,0:00:18.31,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why he said that."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:22.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.92,0:00:25.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:27.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hints from Ayumi's illustrated \Ndiary save the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Catch that jewel thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.37,0:00:31.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:32.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.70,0:00:35.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:20.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(405,1)}The Case of Ayumi's Illustrated Diary
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.45,0:02:18.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of Ayumi's Illustrated Diary!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:28.87,Jewelry Kaneko,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:28.87,Ogino Produce Store,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.72,0:02:25.32,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun noticed the jewel thief
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.32,0:02:28.70,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,while walking through a shopping \Narea on the way to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.04,0:02:38.12,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.69,0:02:41.55,DCMain,MITSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is it your illustrated diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.30,0:02:44.24,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.24,0:02:47.26,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm never sure what to write each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.72,0:02:49.06,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you guys do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.28,0:02:53.19,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Just write about whatever \Nyou want to eat that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:56.98,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Like grilled eel in a bowl, or grilled \Neel in a box, or quartered grilled eel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.31,0:02:58.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.22,0:03:02.60,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,When I can't decide, I go for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.60,0:03:05.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you end up writing \Nthe same thing every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.96,0:03:07.34,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.12,0:03:08.62,Today,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Today I went for a walk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:08.62,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I can write something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.20,0:03:10.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:12.45,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.45,0:03:13.84,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:18.01,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,A quick search online yields plenty of \Nideas, like the weather or whatever else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:22.30,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You simply have to choose whatever \Nyou like from among the options.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:24.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't sound right either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.25,0:03:28.31,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, jeez. What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.13,0:03:31.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Carefully observe all kinds of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:34.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll discover the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:35.39,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.37,0:03:41.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You should observe your \Nsurroundings in your own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.43,0:03:44.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll find \Nsomething to write about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.30,0:03:49.50,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Thanks, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.94,0:03:52.10,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.86,0:03:54.88,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bunch of people over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:55.88,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.51,0:03:58.38,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:07.89,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What does Kaneko-san plan to do \Nby stocking something this nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.89,0:04:11.04,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,He said he hoped it would \Nrevitalize the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:13.39,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,What if someone steals it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:17.52,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm not certain, but it's probably insured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:17.52,Fujioka,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(231,1)}Fujioka Yuji (28)\NCourier
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.82,0:04:20.53,Ogino,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)}Ogino Masako (38)\NGrocer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:20.53,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Right. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.94,0:04:24.41,Nishimura,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(237,438)}Nishimura Kidaharu (65)\NCafe Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:25.70,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Then it'd be no skin off Kaneko-san's \Nnose if it were stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.33,0:04:30.04,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:35.25,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder how much that \Nwatch would sell for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:41.62,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you sold it so it couldn't be \Ntraced, it'd probably go for at least 70 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:43.33,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,70 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.33,0:04:44.26,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:47.76,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you can get several times the market \Nprice if you sell it to a collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.96,0:04:52.77,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,If I got that much money,\NI'd take my family to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:56.09,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what drew the small crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.45,0:04:57.31,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Speaking of which, did you win that trip \Nto Hawaii you mentioned the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.55,0:04:59.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.80,0:04:59.94,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.01,0:05:01.32,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's so shiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:01.46,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I hope you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.46,0:05:04.78,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'd like to win a trip to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:04.78,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how many eel bowls this is worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.50,0:05:08.26,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.88,0:05:11.83,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it almost time for school? Get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.83,0:05:13.50,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.53,0:05:17.04,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,According to Conan-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:23.81,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,the jewel thief was trying to steal the \Nbig shiny watch from Jewelry Kaneko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.26,0:05:30.30,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Diamond Limited Tourbillon Cage No. 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.77,0:05:37.65,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Made by renowned watchmaker Soumillon, \Nthere's only five of them in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.14,0:05:41.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder the grocer was so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.55,0:05:48.42,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite the luxury watch \Nfor a small town jeweler.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:51.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Enough to create a commotion \Namong ordinary people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:56.64,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it doesn't become the target \Nof any ill-intentioned people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.61,0:06:05.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you beat that game?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.25,0:06:06.62,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:07.47,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.47,0:06:08.82,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:09.97,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.38,0:06:13.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you lock your doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:14.22,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:15.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:18.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.93,0:06:21.48,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:24.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it about the luxury watch \Nat the store next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.70,0:06:27.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:29.53,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Then what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.80,0:06:35.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There have been a lot of \Nburglaries in this area lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.41,0:06:39.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm handing out these fliers \Nto alert the locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:44.59,Rash of Burglaries,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an2}Rash of Burglaries!! \N{\c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Please be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.03,0:06:47.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Anyway, that's why we're \Nhanding out these fliers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:48.22,Kaneko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(237,438)}Kaneko Keita (57)\NJewelry Store Proprietor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.44,0:06:51.09,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you, I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:06:56.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister. We heard the watch in \Nyour store window is really expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:58.77,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.77,0:06:59.98,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:04.76,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. After all, you seem to be \Nfriends with this police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.97,0:07:17.29,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Soumillon's masterpiece from \Nthe height of his career.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.57,0:07:22.55,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Diamond Limited Tourbillon Cage No. 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.55,0:07:24.88,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Beautiful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.08,0:07:26.55,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:29.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It looks different up close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:30.88,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's so sparkly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:35.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Kaneko-san, how's your security?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:37.27,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.27,0:07:40.02,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,My security is absolutely secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:44.27,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I have security cameras covering \Nevery inch of the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.60,0:07:48.28,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,The footage is stored on the cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:51.83,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,so you don't need to worry \Nabout intruders erasing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.69,0:07:57.28,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Outside of business hours,\NI keep the sturdy shutters closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:08:00.90,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I also have infrared and \Npressure sensors installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.80,0:08:06.31,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,The store window where the watch is \Ndisplayed is made of tempered glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.31,0:08:10.15,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,and a code is required to open this door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.11,0:08:17.90,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,All of these systems are \Nmonitored by computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.90,0:08:22.81,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,If anything happens, the security \Ncompany will come running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.16,0:08:30.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. With security this tight, it's not \Npossible for your average burglar to break in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:31.69,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.02,0:08:35.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But nothing's for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.01,0:08:37.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.36,0:08:38.57,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.03,0:08:41.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.70,0:08:43.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Now then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:44.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kids—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.60,0:08:45.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:49.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think that watch is at risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.90,0:08:54.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But security is tight,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:58.85,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and it's hard to imagine jewelry theft \Ngoing well in this day and age.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.46,0:09:03.07,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.65,0:09:07.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not busy, could you \Nhelp me hand out these fliers?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:10.72,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.36,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, w-wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:17.11,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of note happened for \Nseveral days after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:19.23,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.45,0:09:23.70,Cafe Haronbo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(734,1)}Cafe \NHaronbo
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.65,0:09:26.22,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Hup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.47,0:09:30.09,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.52,0:09:32.59,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.01,0:09:35.86,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take any detours. \NHead straight to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.86,0:09:37.50,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.68,0:09:49.42,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.42,0:09:51.59,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's construction work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.94,0:10:00.96,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like they're renovating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.96,0:10:01.49,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:05.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:07.22,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Suspicious? Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.22,0:10:12.54,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Like pretending to do construction work \Nso they can rob the jewelry store?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:15.10,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that true, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:17.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.76,0:10:20.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check it out for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.16,0:10:21.97,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:24.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.56,0:10:29.36,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:35.35,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, I'm renovating my store.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:39.70,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,The president of the engineering \Nfirm over there is named Kumazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.07,0:10:44.94,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,We've known each other since middle school, \Nso he's given me a special discount.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.93,0:10:47.89,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is it possible that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.89,0:10:49.37,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That you're pretending to renovate your store
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:52.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,so you can steal the watch \Nfrom the jeweler next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:52.66,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.66,0:10:55.10,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be rude, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.62,0:10:58.59,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Marvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.22,0:11:04.09,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,If I punched a hole in that wall \Nand stole some jewels, I'd be rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.09,0:11:07.21,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Then I could open a store overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.21,0:11:08.60,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.59,0:11:14.32,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll become a professional thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:19.21,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.87,0:11:23.87,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I may not look like it, but the \Nonly thing I can do is make coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.87,0:11:26.66,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too clumsy to be a thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:29.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:33.75,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,They're Kumazawa's sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:36.75,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I've known them since they were in diapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.61,0:11:39.72,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,You suspect them, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.89,0:11:41.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.04,0:11:43.09,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:44.81,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Cheetah Transport here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.81,0:11:46.97,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.97,0:11:50.04,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you sign or stamp here, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.04,0:11:51.02,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.48,0:11:53.98,cafe,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Café Haronbo
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.26,0:11:54.42,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.98,0:11:58.98,cafe - Copy,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Café Haronbo
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.42,0:11:56.64,DCMain,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Come back once we've finished renovations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:58.06,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.68,0:12:03.78,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Well? You heard what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.32,0:12:06.17,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a little suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.17,0:12:08.79,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't seem like a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.18,0:12:11.01,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The juice was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:18.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's certainly risky to rob \Nthe jewelry store next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.77,0:12:21.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he made jokes about it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.45,0:12:24.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what he actually thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:27.80,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,What's got you kids down?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.35,0:12:29.41,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.28,0:12:30.77,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.76,0:12:33.60,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oranges?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.78,0:12:35.13,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,On the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.13,0:12:37.86,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Have some oranges and cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.96,0:12:41.39,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Head home once you finish those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.39,0:12:42.61,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.18,0:12:46.03,DCMain,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, ma'am. What can I get you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.17,0:12:55.62,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then nothing in particular \Nhappened for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:53.00,Aloha,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(62,1)}Aloha
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:55.92,Jewelry Kaneko,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(321,160)\fad(148,1)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:55.92,Ogino Produce Store,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(126,169)}Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:59.54,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But while Conan-kun thought hard about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.54,0:13:03.15,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit's plans were steadily advancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:05.93,Jewelry Kaneko Large,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(188,1)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.24,0:13:12.67,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean there wasn't anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:14.86,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,who thought about stealing that watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.86,0:13:16.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.11,0:13:17.24,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:21.44,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I think the owner of the café is suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.74,0:13:25.20,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think the contractors are suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:29.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What if it's actually the \Nlady from the produce store?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.93,0:13:34.12,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You should also consider the possibility \Nthat the jeweler might pretend to rob himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:38.12,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He might do it for the insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.41,0:13:42.38,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, Haibara-san. \NIt's certainly possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:47.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all keep an eye out \Nso there is no burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:50.02,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:14:00.54,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,With no crime, there wasn't \Nanything Conan-kun could do,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:05.49,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,but several days later,\Nthat fateful day would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.19,0:14:29.35,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.08,0:14:32.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:35.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, read this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.52,0:14:39.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your illustrated diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.63,0:14:49.32,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:49.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.17,0:14:55.14,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I think I got better \Nat keeping an illustrated diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:14:56.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:15:00.25,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget what you told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.56,0:15:06.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Carefully observe all kinds of things, \Nand you'll discover the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.07,0:15:06.86,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.94,0:15:12.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You should observe your \Nsurroundings in your own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.10,0:15:16.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll find \Nsomething to write about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.86,0:15:18.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.69,0:15:19.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:26.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, like you said, I've been \Ncarefully observing my surroundings every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.85,0:15:32.32,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,When I started writing exactly what \NI saw and felt, I got better at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:35.41,Jewelry Kaneko,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(330,162)\frz9.006}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:35.41,Ogino Produce Store,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz9.762\pos(142,197)}Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:35.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.21,0:15:38.29,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:41.76,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.47,0:15:43.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:49.30,Aloha,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz334.4\org(271,97)\frx20\fry334\pos(245,115)}Aloha
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:46.25,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What about that drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:49.30,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Michiyo-chan from \Nthe class next door—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:52.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-chan, what's Michiyo-chan's family name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.07,0:15:55.05,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's Ogino.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.57,0:15:57.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.27,0:15:58.38,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.38,0:15:59.64,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:04.56,Ogino Produce Large,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.54,0:16:10.27,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into you, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:14.22,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like you figured something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:15.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:17.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.65,0:16:18.55,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.22,0:16:22.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a lot I need\Nto confirm, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:24.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that's definitely it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:29.25,Jewelry Kaneko Large,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18\frz354.4\pos(410,227)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:29.25,Ogino Produce Large,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\frz354.3\pos(153,166)}Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:02.29,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,Almost. I'm almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.51,0:17:06.29,DCMain,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,You just wait, my little jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.80,0:18:05.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.09,0:18:09.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You nearly pulled it off. Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:14.16,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You can't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.16,0:18:16.03,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We've already called the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.52,0:18:17.34,DCMain,CULRPIT,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.75,0:18:24.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You heard an expensive luxury watch \Nwas on display at Jewelry Kaneko.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.85,0:18:26.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,While waiting to see what would happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:31.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you heard Café Haronbo was renovating \Nits store and came up with your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.46,0:18:34.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.95,0:18:39.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Cheetah Transport courier Fujioka Yuji-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.02,0:18:43.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This was the plan you came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:49.17,Jewelry Kaneko Large,MIDDLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1487,1)\fs24\pos(169,176)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.25,0:18:47.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The renovation work being done at \Nthe café next to the jewelry store
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:50.44,Cafe Haronbo,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(458,185)\fad(399,1)}Café Haronbo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.49,0:18:48.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,would generate a lot of noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:56.57,Ogino Produce Large,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\fad(1655,1)\pos(152,167)}Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:51.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You decided to use that noise as a camouflage
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.44,0:18:56.57,Jewelry Kaneko Large,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\fad(690,1)\pos(487,169)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.85,0:18:55.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to enter the jeweler from the \Nproduce store on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.23,0:19:00.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the cafe was \Nundergoing renovations,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.23,0:19:03.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how much noise you \Nmade, no one would suspect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.01,0:19:08.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you just needed the produce \Nstore workers to go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.06,0:19:15.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You probably learned the grocer loves \Nprize contests from that conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.69,0:19:21.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and invited her and her family to Hawaii \Nby lying and telling her she'd won a prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.61,0:19:28.06,DCItalic,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you sold it so it couldn't be \Ntraced, it'd probably go for at least 70 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:29.86,DCItalic,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,70 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.86,0:19:30.74,DCItalic,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.74,0:19:34.11,DCItalic,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you can get several times the market \Nprice if you sell it to a collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.74,0:19:39.49,DCItalic,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,If I got that much money, I'd \Ntake my family to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.96,0:19:44.31,DCItalic,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, did you win that trip \Nto Hawaii you mentioned the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.31,0:19:46.49,DCItalic,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:49.50,DCItalic,NISHIMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:51.99,DCItalic,OGINO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to win a trip to Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.81,0:19:54.80,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,H-How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:56.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:19:59.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you didn't see that note she posted?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:00.26,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.83,0:20:07.06,DCMain,MITSUHIUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It says the shop is temporary closed \Nbecause they're on a family trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:07.26,Temporarily Closed,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Temporarily Closed\N\NThe shop will be temporarily closed from \N11/30 to 12/8 due to a family vacation\N\NOgino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.82,0:20:17.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That must've been a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:23.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been digging for five days since \Nthey went on their trip, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.45,0:20:24.03,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.42,0:20:25.78,DCMain,FUJIOKA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.22,0:20:28.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Edogawa Conan—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:29.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshida Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.67,0:20:30.16,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.33,0:20:32.67,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Kojima Genta.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:33.92,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuburaya Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.92,0:20:38.30,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,We are the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.23,0:20:39.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.56,0:20:44.88,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the case was solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.28,0:20:51.04,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit Fujioka-san was \Narrested by Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:56.31,Aloha,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(106,1)}Aloha
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.78,0:20:56.87,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun said he figured \Nout the culprit's trick
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:21:02.32,Jewelry Kaneko,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(195,1)\pos(320,162)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:21:02.32,Ogino Produce Store,LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(125,171)}Ogino Produce Store
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:21:02.58,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,from my illustrations of Michiyo-chan \Nand the three buildings in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:13.96,sign_30270_331_Jewelry_Kaneko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(146,1)\pos(489,112)}Jewelry Kaneko
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.12,0:21:07.26,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He deduced that the culprit \Nmust know a lot about the area
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.26,0:21:10.14,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,and began to suspect Fujioka-san the courier
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.14,0:21:13.70,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,who was having a conversation \Nin front of the jeweler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.04,0:21:20.92,Aloha,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(581,72)}Fujioka Yuji
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.19,0:21:16.21,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the deciding factor
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:21.14,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,was that he accurately named \Nthe black market price.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:25.88,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun called the \NCheetah Transport company
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.88,0:21:30.75,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,and determined that Fujioka-san \Nhad missed work for five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.03,0:21:39.89,Aloha,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20\pos(336,96)}Illustrated Diary
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.56,0:21:35.31,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun said he couldn't \Nhave solved this case
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:38.96,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,without my illustrated diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.96,0:21:40.37,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.37,0:21:47.60,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was my first big \Nsuccess as a member of the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:48.71,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.61,0:21:59.00,Detective Boys Win,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord4\pos(324,116)}Detective Boys Win!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.19,0:21:52.70,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how the Detective Boys
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.70,0:21:57.39,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,prevented a burglary before it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.00,0:23:24.59,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HE5CE9D&}Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:27.32,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi treated us to lots of tasty \Nfood at Poirot to thank us for preventing a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:27.38,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\fs26\fnArial\bord3\shad0\c&H34DAF5&\pos(415,86)\fad(1902,1)}Coffee {\c&H6761E4&}Poirot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.32,0:23:29.91,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.65,0:23:35.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait. This isn't an \Nall-you-can-eat restaurant, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.44,0:23:38.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But can't Ayumi-chan eat all she wants?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.45,0:23:39.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.55,0:23:41.77,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HF1E9E3&\3c&HADA6A0&}Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.65,0:23:51.36,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,He's really a great detective \Nwho can solve any case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.84,0:23:56.24,DCMain,MAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you show a little more \Nconsideration for your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.68,0:24:00.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You mentioned something \Nabout the gears of tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.88,0:24:04.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't you who turned \Nthem, but the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.30,0:24:07.50,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Automatic Tragedy (Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.52,0:24:13.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NAutomatic Tragedy, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:34.95,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Answering Machine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.44,0:24:32.90,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:34.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An answering machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.77,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's play with tin can phones!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:39.95,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
